   "source": [
    "# RLTF-SD Training Pipeline\n",
    "-------------------------------------\n",
    "This notebook serves as the primary orchestration script for the RLTF-SD paper implementation.\n",
    "\n",
    "Why a notebook?\n",
    "The user requested a notebook-centric or modular approach. A notebook is the easiest way to load models interactively, inspect the dataset, and launch the custom `src.trainer.RLTF_SD_Trainer` without writing massive argparse CLI scripts.\n",
    "\n",
    "It covers:\n",
    "1. Loading the student model (Llama-3-8B-Instruct is recommended by the paper, though we might use a smaller model for memory limits).\n",
    "2. Loading the dataset using our `data.py`.\n",
    "3. Setting the `GRPOConfig` training arguments.\n",
    "4. Initializing the custom `RLTF_SD_Trainer`.\n",
    "5. Starting the Reinforcement Learning loop.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4b1f9770",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer\n",
    "from trl import GRPOConfig\n",
    "\n",
    "from src.data import load_data\n",
    "from src.trainer import RLTF_SD_Trainer\n",
    "\n",
    "# Setup device\n",
    "device = \"cuda\" if torch.cuda.is_available() else \"cpu\"\n",
    "print(f\"Using device: {device}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d75fd005",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 1. Load the Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3dc196e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load the MATH-500 dataset formatted with the initial turn 1 prompt (x_0)\n",
    "dataset = load_data()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split into train and eval (just for demonstration, paper trains on train set and evaluates on eval)\n",
    "train_dataset = dataset[\"train\"] if \"train\" in dataset else dataset\n",
    "eval_dataset = dataset[\"test\"] if \"test\" in dataset else dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Train size: {len(train_dataset)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Example prompt: {train_dataset[0]['prompt'][:100]}...\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0a62fb3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2. Load the Student Model"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b3c2654d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Using a small model for testing. The paper uses Qwen2.5-Math-7B or Llama-3-8b-Instruct.\n",
    "# For free-tier constraints, a 1.5B or 3B model is recommended if you have an 24GB GPU, or run in 4/8-bit!\n",
    "model_id = \"Qwen/Qwen2.5-Math-1.5B-Instruct\"\n",
    "\n",
    "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_id)\n",
    "# Ensure pad token is set for batched generation\n",
    "if tokenizer.pad_token is None:\n",
    "    tokenizer.pad_token = tokenizer.eos_token\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load model in bfloat16 to save memory\n",
    "model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    model_id,\n",
    "    torch_dtype=torch.bfloat16,\n",
    "    device_map=\"auto\"\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8b3b937c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3. Initialize Training Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e76dacd9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# We use GRPOConfig to pass all Proximal Policy Optimization hyperparameters\n",
    "# The paper uses: KL penalty coefficient \\beta = 0.01, PPO clipping \\epsilon = 0.2\n",
    "training_args = GRPOConfig(\n",
    "    output_dir=\"rltf_sd_checkpoints\",\n",
    "    learning_rate=1e-6, # Small LR recommended for RL\n",
    "    num_train_epochs=1,\n",
    "    per_device_train_batch_size=2,\n",
    "    gradient_accumulation_steps=4,\n",
    "    max_completion_length=512, # Max length of the generated reasoning trace\n",
    "    num_generations=4, # Number of generations to sample per prompt for the baseline mean(r_0)\n",
    "    beta=0.01,         # KL Divergence Penalty\n",
    "    save_steps=10,\n",
    "    logging_steps=1,\n",
    "    remove_unused_columns=False, # Essential: keep the 'prompt' and 'ground_truth' columns!\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa837b3d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 4. Run the RLTF-SD Trainer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dacc82e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize our custom trainer!\n",
    "# Notice we don't pass `reward_funcs` because we baked the multi-turn rewards\n",
    "# directly into the overridden `_generate_and_score_completions` inside the trainer!\n",
    "trainer = RLTF_SD_Trainer(\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    train_dataset=train_dataset,\n",
    "    eval_dataset=eval_dataset,\n",
    "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n",
    "    args=training_args,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Starting 2-Turn RLTF-SD Training Loop...\")\n",
    "# trainer.train() # Uncomment to run (requires GPU)\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
